Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharpish turn. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Production date: 124 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Teisamenos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, Taposiris Magna (SCA 156).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1146)
